Selecting Elements

// Select all inputs, buttons, and containers


Add New Expense

When “Add Expense” button is clicked:

Get input values (title, category, amount)

Create an expense object (with unique id)

Save it to localStorage

Re-render all expenses

Update total spent

Display All Expenses

When page loads (DOMContentLoaded), load data from localStorage

For each expense → create .expense-card dynamically and append

Filter Expenses

When dropdown filterCategory changes:

Show only expenses matching the selected category

If “All”, show all

Delete Expense

Each card has a delete button

On click → remove that expense from both DOM and localStorage

Update total

Update Total

Every time expenses are added or deleted → recalculate total amount

Display it inside #totalAmount